RED BURGUNDY An Appraisal of the 1964 Vintage.

In Burgundy, the growers were more fortunate than in Bordeaux for there was no rain during the harvest and quality, in general, proved excellent. Like the 1959s, the Reds have great charm and fruit, which was apparent from the very beginning, but the ’64s appear to assert more character. On the whole, the 1964 red burgundies are firmer, and with more depth and

staying power than the ’59’s, In general, Burgundy, rather than Bordeaux, fared better in 1964.
